La Jarocita.dish-name-1: Carnitas huarache with everything, black beans
La Jarocita.dish-notes-1: You can't go wrong here, try anything!
La Jarocita.dish-notes-2: A great cart that offers tofu! Not a very common thing for mexican food, so if you are a veggie burrito lover, this one is worth trying. You can ask for no dairy, and also add potatoes if you wish. They are super nice!

Huong's.dish-notes-1: Possibly the best-value food deal in PDX. $4 for a full meal. They will offer to have the peanuts in the sandwich (recommended) or on the side.
Huong's.dish-notes-2: Hands down best value for a really great sandwich. 4$ for a full meal. This is the vegetarian alternative to the meat options, but I haven't been able to confirm if it's totally vegan. The (amazingly delicious) sauce they put on it might contain fish sauce.

Rolling Gourmet Fusion.dish-notes-1: Seriously, any of them. And any 2 side items. Depending on which rolls you order, this can be a gluten free meal.

808 Grinds.dish-notes-1: Or anything, their menu is simple. Even the mac salad is good. Try the different sauces.

Gyro Place.dish-notes-1: Or the kafta gyro if you're not starving (the rice plates are huge and come with salad and hummus) - or the unique falafel.
Gyro Place.dish-notes-2: This comes with a salad, hummus, rice, falafel, tzaziki, sauces, and pita upon request. Very good food, and super nice folks.

Nong's Kao Man Gai.dish-notes-1: Delicious pressure-cooked chicken and rice. Comes with a bowl of ginger sauce and a bowl of soup. Order it spicy if you dare! Also: great Thai iced-tea & iced-coffee.

Noodle House.dish-notes-2: I have not confirmed if the noodles are vegan, but this is a great vegetarian option at a solid cart. Get it spicy.

E-San.dish-notes-1: I think this is the best Pad Thai deal around, these folks know what they're doing (there will likely be a line for this cart). Any of the menu items can be made vegetarian, and also vegan (with no egg or fish sauce). Having tried it all 3 ways, I can say it has been consistently good.
E-San.dish-notes-2: This is a really tasty stir fry, something a little different that took me a while to try - and now its my favorite! Can be made vegetarian or vegan upon request, also ask for brown rice if you prefer.

Grilled Cheese Grill.dish-notes-1: Safe comfort food here. Can be made with vegan substitutions!

Tito's Burritos.dish-notes-1: One of my favorite places to get a chicken burrito. They really do a So-Cal style burrito justice here in Portland where that can be hard to find. Salsas are recommended.
Tito's Burritos.dish-notes-2: Solid veggie burrito, can be made vegan upon request. The red and green sauce here are great.

Wolf and Bear's.dish-notes-1: Portland-style Mediterranean food. This wrap has really great fresh veggies (fried egg plant too!), crispy falafel, and some an amazing tahini sauce with hummus.
Wolf and Bear's.dish-notes-2: Really tasty salad that will satisfy your hunger. I usually add a couple falafel.

The Whole Bowl.dish-notes-1: This is the only thing they serve, in 2 sizes. One of Portland's most popular food carts, with a bunch of locations all over town. The sauce is reknowned and makes a simple dish something special. Can be requested vegan, they will give you extra avocado.

Burger Stevens.dish-notes-1: high quality standard burgers and fries. Everything at this cart is good. The veggie burger can be made vegan with avocado spread. Fries are $3 extra but so worth it.
Burger Stevens.dish-notes-2: High quality standard burgers and fries. This cart offers a full list of add-ons (avocado, egg, bacon, etc.). You can do a double here as well.

Fried Egg I'm In Love.dish-notes-1: Their signature dish, can be made vegatarian with veggie sausage.

Stretch the Noodle.dish-notes-1: This place is pretty special. The noodles are hand made - right in front of you! Pretty cool to see, but it does take a little bit. Try to avoid lunch rush. Tofu and veggies option is great, but they have meat versions as well as other dishes that look great.

Greenleaf.dish-notes-1: you can ask for gluten free oatmeal for an extra few bucks. located off pioneer square. absolutely two meals for the price of one.

Tasty n Alder.dish-notes-1: Literally anything you get will be good. This place can get full for lunch, but it's great for a more upscale sit-down lunch.

La Jarocha.dish-notes-1: A little bit of a walk, but worth it for a good sit down lunch. The menu doesn't seem to be very vegetarian-friendly but it might be worth calling about.

Bamboo Sushi.dish-notes-1: A bit expensive, but is known as one of the best places to get sushi in town. This dish can be served without albacore, making it vegan, and it is also very good.

Shigezo.dish-notes-1: The menu here is vegetarian, vegan, and gluten-free friendly, just talk to your server. Known for the Ramen, but everything else is good. This is an excellent place for sushi.

Habibi.dish-notes-1: Great place for a sit-down group lunch, and the menu is very diverse with every section split into vegan, vegetarian and meat. It's a short walk and they usually have a table. Gluten-free folks talk to your server, but for the most part just avoid the bread.

Mayas Taqueria.dish-notes-1: Easy place to walk in and order. solid food, burritos come with chips and salsa. Can be requested vegan, and the habenero salsa is excellent.

Southpark.dish-notes-1: A sit-down that is very close, and serves quality food. They are known for their clam chowder, but I hear pretty much everything else is good too!
Southpark.dish-notes-2: A go-to dish, really delicious. Basically tied with the clam chowder in quality.

Darsalam.dish-notes-1: Really good buffet style lunch, affordable, and pretty close.

Addys Sandwich Bar.dish-notes-1: This sandwich is amazing. I recommend the baguette version, but you can order in various sandwich forms. They have a nice little deli selection of salads and things to choose from.
Addys Sandwich Bar.dish-notes-2: I love this place. I recommend the baguette version, but you can order in various sandwich forms. They have a nice little deli selection of salads and things to choose from.

Thai Peacock.dish-notes-1: Really great sit down lunch spot, with a full menu. Gets a little busy in there, but it is highly recommended for pretty much any dish. One of the best Thai places in town.
